===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪdʒɪt|-ɪdʒɪt]]

===Noun===
'''midget'''  (''plural:'' '''[[midgets]]''')

# A normally proportioned person with small stature, usually defined as reaching an adult height less than 4'10".
#(''derogatory'') Any short person.
#(''[[attributively]]'') That is a small version of something; [[miniature]]
#:''the '''midget''' pony''
#(''loosely'') Any small swarming insect similar to the mosquito; a [[midge]]

====Usage notes====
*The term '''midget''' to refer to a person of small stature is considered offensive by many.
*Used for an insect, this is an variation on '''[[midge]]''' that is incorrect but commonly used.

====Synonyms====
*(''person below 4'10"''): [[dwarf]] (''loosely'')
*(''derogatory: any small person''): [[dwarf]], [[short-arse]], [[shortie]]/[[shorty]], [[tich]]/[[titch]], [[vertically challenged]] person (''humorous'')
*(''miniature''): [[dwarf]]

====Antonyms====
*(''derogatory: any small person''): [[giant]]
*(''miniature''): [[giant]]

